<tr>
<th colspan="2" style="background:#d1dbdf; font-size:120%;">Review scores</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Source</th>
<th>Rating</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="Allmusic" title="Allmusic">Allmusic</a></td>
<td style="vertical-align:middle"><span style="white-space:nowrap" title="5/5 stars"><img alt="5/5 stars" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/11px-Star_full.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/17px-Star_full.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/22px-Star_full.svg.png 2x" /><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/11px-Star_full.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/17px-Star_full.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/22px-Star_full.svg.png 2x" /><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/11px-Star_full.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/17px-Star_full.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/22px-Star_full.svg.png 2x" /><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/11px-Star_full.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/17px-Star_full.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/22px-Star_full.svg.png 2x" /><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/11px-Star_full.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/17px-Star_full.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/22px-Star_full.svg.png 2x" /></span><sup id="cite_ref-36" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-36"><span>[</span>36<span>]</span></a></sup></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i><a href="Drowned_In_Sound" title="Drowned In Sound" class="mw-redirect">Drowned In Sound</a></i></td>
<td style="vertical-align:middle">(10/10)<sup id="cite_ref-37" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-37"><span>[</span>37<span>]</span></a></sup></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i><a href="Rolling_Stone" title="Rolling Stone">Rolling Stone</a></i></td>
<td style="vertical-align:middle"><span style="white-space:nowrap" title="4.5/5 stars"><img alt="4.5/5 stars" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/11px-Star_full.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/17px-Star_full.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/22px-Star_full.svg.png 2x" /><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/11px-Star_full.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/17px-Star_full.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/22px-Star_full.svg.png 2x" /><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/11px-Star_full.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/17px-Star_full.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/22px-Star_full.svg.png 2x" /><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/11px-Star_full.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/17px-Star_full.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Star_full.svg/22px-Star_full.svg.png 2x" /><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Star_half.svg/11px-Star_half.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Star_half.svg/17px-Star_half.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Star_half.svg/22px-Star_half.svg.png 2x" /></span><sup id="cite_ref-38" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-38"><span>[</span>38<span>]</span></a></sup></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="Robert_Christgau" title="Robert Christgau">Robert Christgau</a></td>
<td style="vertical-align:middle">A−<sup id="cite_ref-39" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-39"><span>[</span>39<span>]</span></a></sup></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><i>Metal Box</i> is now considered a <a href="Post-punk" title="Post-punk">post-punk</a> classic, and is very critically acclaimed. Allmusic gave it a five star rating, saying "PIL managed to avoid boundaries for the first four years of their existence, and Metal Box is undoubtedly the apex" and that it "hardly [sounds] like anything of the past, present, or future". The reviewer, Andy Kellman, also compared it to the works of <a href="Captain_Beefheart" title="Captain Beefheart">Captain Beefheart</a> and <a href="Can_(band)" title="Can (band)">Can</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-40" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-40"><span>[</span>40<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="Drowned_In_Sound" title="Drowned In Sound" class="mw-redirect">Drowned In Sound</a> also gave it a perfect score, with reviewer Mark Ward stating "it tears away from Lydon’s sweaty punk roots and into the cold chambers of dub evoked by Can, the more outré electronics of <a href="David_Bowie" title="David Bowie">Bowie’s</a> Berlin years and the coruscating post-punk sound that guitarist Levene was in the process of pioneering" and that "if you don’t yet have a copy, you really should".<sup id="cite_ref-41" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-41"><span>[</span>41<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>In 2003, the album was inducted into <a href="Rolling_Stone" title="Rolling Stone">Rolling Stone's</a> <a href="The_500_Greatest_Albums_of_All_Time" title="The 500 Greatest Albums of All Time" class="mw-redirect">500 Greatest Albums Of All Time</a> list at #469, the magazine calling it "eerie, futuristic art punk with dub bass and slashing guitar".<sup id="cite_ref-42" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-42"><span>[</span>42<span>]</span></a></sup> In 2002, <a href="Pitchfork_Media" title="Pitchfork Media">Pitchfork Media</a> ranked <i>Metal Box</i> at #19 on its "Top 100 Albums of the 1980s".<sup id="cite_ref-43" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-43"><span>[</span>43<span>]</span></a></sup> It was also, along with their debut album, included in the book <a href="1001_Albums_You_Must_Hear_Before_You_Die" title="1001 Albums You Must Hear Before You Die">1001 Albums You Must Hear Before You Die</a>, with the reviewer Stevie Chick saying "the abrasive textures and powerful sounds they discovered...would influence all manner of experimental music for decades to come", while describing it as "cold dank, unforgiving, subterranean. The songs Albatross, Poptones, Careering, Chant and Radio 4 were selected as "key tracks".<sup id="cite_ref-44" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-44"><span>[</span>44<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Metal_Box&action=edit&section=6.php.html" title="Edit section: Track listing">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Track_listing">Track listing</span></h2>
